flowchart LR
  contributor["Contributor or agent"]:::person
  reviewer["Reviewer or maintainer"]:::person
  adapter_user["Codex, Claude Code, and opencode user"]:::person
  repo["RigorLoop repository<br/>[Git-first workflow and adapter starter kit]"]:::system
  git["Git and PR review<br/>[Review platform]"]:::external
  execution["Local shell and GitHub Actions<br/>[Validation execution]"]:::external
  package_runner["npm/npx package runner<br/>[CLI delivery surface]"]:::external
  npm_registry["npm registry<br/>[Public CLI package registry]"]:::external
  package_surface["Generated adapter package consumers<br/>[External runtime surfaces]"]:::external
  release_assets["GitHub release assets<br/>[Adapter archives and metadata]"]:::external

  contributor -->|uses the standard workflow or isolated manual skill invocations to author changes in| repo
  contributor -->|runs the RigorLoop CLI from| package_runner
  reviewer -->|reviews selected architecture surface, C4 views, ADRs, and evidence in| repo
  repo -->|publishes reviewable branch and PR history through| git
  repo -->|validates lifecycle, metadata, drift, and diagram source through| execution
  repo -->|packages the CLI candidate and bundled adapter metadata for| package_runner
  repo -->|publishes the verified CLI package to| npm_registry
  npm_registry -->|serves @xiongxianfei/rigorloop to| package_runner
  repo -->|publishes verified adapter archives as| release_assets
  repo -->|generates synchronized project-portable guidance for| package_surface
  package_runner -->|executes init and verifies supported adapter archives against bundled metadata from| repo
  package_runner -->|downloads verified Codex, Claude Code, and opencode adapter archives from| release_assets
  adapter_user -->|installs or copies generated guidance from| package_surface

  classDef person fill:#08427b,stroke:#073b6f,color:#fff
  classDef system fill:#1168bd,stroke:#0e5aa7,color:#fff
  classDef external fill:#999,stroke:#666,color:#fff
  classDef container fill:#438dd5,stroke:#3c7fc0,color:#fff
